(43, 17, 1, 43, 13, 31, 32, 'glorify thy Son', 'Glorification of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of the Son, with Jesus stating that the hour has come for this glorification. The connection lies in the mutual glorification between the Son and the Father, highlighting their relationship.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 43, 17, 4, 5, 'glorify thy Son', 'Glorification of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification. In the source verse, Jesus asks the Father to glorify Him, while in the target passage, He states that He has glorified the Father and requests to be glorified again.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 50, 2, 9, 11, 'glorify thy Son', 'Exaltation and Glory of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification. In John 17:1, Jesus asks to be glorified, while Philippians 2:9-11 describes how God has highly exalted Him, leading to universal acknowledgment of His lordship.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 44, 3, 13, 13, 'glorify thy Son', 'Glorification of the Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification present in both passages. In John 17:1, Jesus asks to be glorified, while Acts 3:13 states that God has glorified His Son Jesus.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 60, 1, 21, 21, 'glorify thy Son', 'Connection of Glory in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory associated with Jesus. Both passages emphasize the glorification of the Son, linking His resurrection and the faith of believers in God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 19, 121, 1, 2, 'lifted up his eyes', 'Connection of Lifting Eyes', 'This connection highlights the act of lifting eyes to a higher source. Both passages emphasize looking up for help and glorification, linking the divine relationship between the Son and the Father.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 1, 19, 123, 1, 1, 'lifted up his eyes to heaven', 'Connection of Lifting Eyes', 'This connection highlights the act of lifting eyes to heaven in both passages. John 17:1 emphasizes Jesus lifting his eyes to glorify the Father, while Psalms 123:1 expresses a similar act of looking up to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 43, 10, 28, 29, 'that he should give eternal life', 'Eternal Life Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the granting of eternal life to those given by the Father. John 17:2 speaks of Jesus giving eternal life, while John 10:28-29 assures that those who receive it will never perish.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 43, 6, 39, 39, 'as many as thou hast given him', 'Eternal Life and Preservation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of eternal life given to those whom the Father has entrusted to the Son. John 17:2 speaks of giving eternal life, while John 6:39 highlights the assurance that none of those given will be lost.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 27, 7, 14, 14, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life and Dominion', 'This connection highlights the themes of power and eternal authority in both passages. John 17:2 speaks of giving eternal life, while Daniel 7:14 describes an everlasting dominion and kingdom.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'power over all flesh', 'Power Given to Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of power given to Jesus. Both passages emphasize the authority Jesus possesses over all flesh and in heaven and earth.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 58, 2, 8, 9, 'that he should give eternal life', 'Connection of Authority and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Jesus over all creation and his role in providing eternal life. John 17:2 highlights Jesus'' power to give eternal life, while Hebrews 2:8-9 discusses all things being put under his feet, culminating in his sacrificial death for humanity.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'eternal life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of eternal life given by Jesus. Both passages emphasize that Jesus has the authority to grant eternal life to believers.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 2, 19, 2, 6, 12, 'that he should give eternal life', 'Connection of Authority and Inheritance', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the Son and his role in granting eternal life and inheritance. John 17:2 speaks of the power given to the Son, while Psalms 2:8 mentions the heathen as his inheritance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'the only true God', 'Eternal Life and True God', 'Both passages emphasize knowing ''the true God'' and link this knowledge to eternal life. They highlight the relationship between God, Jesus Christ, and the understanding of true life.', 'theme', 0.937, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 62, 5, 11, 12, 'that they might know thee the only true God', 'Eternal Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize that eternal life is found in knowing God and Jesus Christ. John 17:3 highlights the importance of knowing the true God and Jesus, while 1 John 5:11-12 states that eternal life is in the Son.', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 24, 9, 23, 24, 'that they might know thee', 'Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing God. John 17:3 states that eternal life is to know the only true God, while Jeremiah 9:24 highlights that understanding and knowing the Lord is what truly matters.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 43, 3, 17, 17, 'Jesus Christ, whom thou hast sent', 'Connection of Salvation and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God and salvation through Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus in bringing eternal life and salvation to the world.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 43, 17, 25, 25, 'that they might know thee', 'Knowledge of God and Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God and Jesus Christ. John 17:3 states that eternal life is knowing the only true God and Jesus, while John 17:25 contrasts the world''s lack of knowledge of God with Jesus'' and his disciples'' understanding of his divine mission.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 28, 6, 3, 3, 'know thee the only true God', 'Knowledge of God and Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing God. John 17:3 speaks of knowing the only true God, while Hosea 6:3 encourages following on to know the Lord, suggesting a deepening relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 3, 58, 8, 11, 12, NULL, 'Knowledge of God and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing God. John 17:3 highlights knowing the only true God, while Hebrews 8:11 emphasizes that all shall know Him, linking knowledge of God with His merciful nature.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 4, 43, 4, 34, 34, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the completion of the work given to Jesus. In John 17:4, Jesus states he has finished the work, while in John 4:34, he expresses his purpose to finish that work.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 4, 44, 20, 24, 24, NULL, 'Completion of Divine Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of finishing a divinely appointed task. In John 17:4, Jesus declares he has completed the work given to him, while in Acts 20:24, Paul expresses his desire to finish his course and ministry with joy.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 4, 55, 4, 7, 7, 'finished the work which thou gavest me to do', 'Completion of Divine Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the completion of a divinely assigned task. In John 17:4, the speaker declares having ''finished the work,'' while in 2 Timothy 4:7, the speaker states, ''I have finished my course.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 4, 43, 14, 31, 31, 'the work which thou gavest me to do', 'Obedience to the Father''s Command', 'Both passages emphasize the completion of the work given by the Father. John 17:4 speaks of finishing the work, while John 14:31 highlights obedience to the Father''s commandment.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 4, 42, 22, 37, 37, 'I have finished the work', 'Completion of Divine Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling God''s work. Both passages emphasize the completion of a mission, with John 17:4 stating ''I have finished the work'' and Luke 22:37 referencing the necessity of what is written being accomplished.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 43, 1, 1, 3, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the pre-existence and divine nature of Christ. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Christ had ''before the world was,'' while John 1:1 states that the Word was ''with God'' and ''was God,'' highlighting His eternal existence and divine status.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 51, 1, 15, 17, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the pre-existence and divine authority of Christ. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Christ had before the world, while Colossians 1:15-17 describes Him as the firstborn and creator of all things.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 43, 10, 30, 30, 'glory which I had with thee', 'Unity of Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the shared glory and unity between Jesus and the Father. Both passages emphasize the intimate relationship and oneness that exists, suggesting a divine partnership.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 60, 1, 20, 20, 'the glory which I had with thee before the world was', 'Glory and Foreordination Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the pre-existence of Christ, with John 17:5 referencing the glory Christ had ''before the world was'' and 1 Peter 1:20 mentioning His foreordination ''before the foundation of the world.'' This connection highlights the divine plan and identity of Christ.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 50, 2, 6, 6, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Divine Glory and Equality', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine glory and equality with God. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Jesus had before the world, while Philippians 2:6 emphasizes His equality with God.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 66, 5, 9, 14, 'glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Glory and Worthiness', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory shared between the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize the worthiness of the Lamb to receive glory, reflecting the glory that Jesus speaks of in John 17:5.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine glory shared between the two passages. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Jesus had with the Father before the world was, while Hebrews 1:3 describes Jesus as the brightness of God''s glory.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 43, 17, 26, 26, 'manifested thy name', 'Connection of Manifesting God''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the act of declaring God''s name to the disciples. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' mission to reveal God''s love and presence in them.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 43, 14, 21, 24, 'kept thy word', 'Love and Obedience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping God''s word as a demonstration of love for Him. In John 17:6, Jesus speaks of those who have kept His word, while John 14:21-24 directly links love for Him with obedience to His commandments.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'manifested thy name', 'Understanding of God''s Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God. In John 17:6, Jesus reveals God''s name to those given to Him, while 1 John 5:20 emphasizes understanding Him that is true through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 2, 3, 13, 15, 'manifested thy name', 'Divine Name Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s name being revealed. In John 17:6, Jesus manifests God''s name to His followers, while in Exodus 3:13-15, God reveals His name, ''I AM,'' to Moses, establishing a continuity in the divine identity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 2, 34, 5, 7, 'manifested thy name', 'Manifestation of God''s Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s name being revealed. In both passages, the act of proclaiming or manifesting God''s name signifies His character and relationship with His people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 40, 11, 25, 27, 'manifested thy name', 'Revelation of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the revelation of the Father through the Son. John 17:6 highlights that Jesus has manifested the Father''s name to those given to Him, while Matthew 11:27 states that the Son reveals the Father to whom He wills.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'manifested thy name', 'Light and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of revelation, as both passages speak to the manifestation of God''s glory and knowledge. John 17:6 emphasizes the revealing of God''s name, while 2 Corinthians 4:6 discusses the light of knowledge shining in hearts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 7, 16, 17, 'whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee', 'Connection of Divine Origin', 'Both passages emphasize that the teachings of Jesus are not his own but come from God. This connection highlights the acknowledgment of divine authority in Jesus'' doctrine and mission.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 16, 15, 15, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Ownership', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son regarding divine knowledge and possession. John 17:7 states that all things given to Jesus are from the Father, while John 16:15 asserts that all things the Father has belong to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 8, 28, 28, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee', 'Knowledge of Divine Origin', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding Jesus'' divine origin. Both passages emphasize that Jesus'' teachings and actions are rooted in the relationship with the Father.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 10, 29, 30, 'whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Divine Authority and Unity', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. John 17:7 highlights that all things given to Jesus are from the Father, while John 10:29-30 asserts their unity and the Father''s greater authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 14, 7, 10, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Knowledge of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father. John 17:7 highlights the knowledge of what Jesus has received from the Father, while John 14:7-10 discusses knowing the Father through knowing Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 17, 10, 10, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Divine Ownership and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that all things given to Jesus are from the Father. This connection underscores the unity and shared glory between them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 12, 49, 50, 'whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Command', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that Jesus speaks what the Father has given him. This connection illustrates the unity of purpose and message between them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 43, 17, 14, 14, 'the words which thou gavest me', 'Connection of Divine Words', 'Both passages emphasize the act of giving ''the words'' from God to the disciples. This connection highlights the significance of the disciples'' reception of these words and their separation from the world.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 43, 15, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Knowledge and Friendship', 'This connection highlights the theme of revelation and relationship. Both passages emphasize the idea of making known the words and actions of God, transitioning from servant to friend.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 52, 2, 13, 13, 'received them', 'Connection of Received Words', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving divine words. Both passages emphasize the importance of accepting God''s message as truth, which leads to belief and effective work in the believers.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'thou didst send me', 'Connection of Divine Sending', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine sending, as both passages affirm that the Father sent the Son. John 17:8 emphasizes the belief in Jesus'' divine origin, while 1 John 4:14 testifies to His role as the Saviour sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 20, 1, 3, 3, 'received them', 'Connection of Instruction and Reception', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving instruction. In John 17:8, the disciples receive the words given to them, while Proverbs 1:3 emphasizes the importance of receiving instruction in wisdom and justice.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 20, 8, 10, 10, NULL, 'Value of Divine Instruction', 'This connection highlights the importance of receiving divine words and instruction. Both passages emphasize valuing knowledge and understanding over material wealth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 40, 13, 11, 11, 'the words which thou gavest me', 'Understanding Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of knowledge granted by God. John 17:8 highlights that the disciples have received the words from Jesus, while Matthew 13:11 indicates that understanding the mysteries of the kingdom is given selectively.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 58, 9, 24, 24, 'for them which thou hast given me', 'Intercession for Believers', 'This connection highlights Christ''s role in interceding for those given to Him, as seen in John 17:9. Hebrews 9:24 emphasizes His presence before God on behalf of believers, reinforcing the theme of divine advocacy.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 43, 17, 2, 2, 'thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Giving', 'Both passages emphasize those whom God has given to Jesus. The phrase ''thou hast given him'' in John 17:2 connects with ''them which thou hast given me'' in John 17:9, highlighting the relationship between Jesus and his followers.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 42, 22, 32, 32, 'I pray for them', 'Connection of Intercessory Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of intercessory prayer, as both passages depict Jesus praying for his followers. In John 17:9, Jesus specifically prays for those given to him, while in Luke 22:32, he prays for Peter''s faith, indicating a focus on strengthening his disciples.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 43, 17, 20, 20, 'for them which thou hast given me', 'Connection of Prayer Focus', 'This connection highlights the shift in Jesus'' prayer focus from His immediate disciples to future believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of those given to Him and those who will believe through their word.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 62, 2, 1, 2, 'I pray for them', 'Intercession and Advocacy', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' role as an advocate for believers. In John 17:9, Jesus prays specifically for those given to Him, while 1 John 2:1-2 emphasizes His advocacy for those who sin, indicating His intercessory role.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 62, 5, 19, 19, 'for them which thou hast given me', 'Connection of Believers and the World', 'This connection highlights the distinction between those given to Jesus and the world. Both passages emphasize that believers are separate from the wickedness that characterizes the world.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 66, 20, 15, 15, 'them which thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Selection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection, as John 17:9 emphasizes those given to Jesus, while Revelation 20:15 indicates that only those written in the book of life are spared from judgment. Both passages underscore the distinction between the chosen and the rejected.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 43, 10, 30, 30, 'all mine are thine', 'Unity of Christ and Father', 'Both passages emphasize the unity between Jesus and the Father. In John 17:10, the phrase ''all mine are thine'' reflects a shared identity, while John 10:30 states ''I and my Father are one,'' reinforcing this connection.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 60, 2, 9, 9, NULL, 'Glorification and Chosen Identity', 'This connection highlights the theme of belonging and identity in Christ. Both passages emphasize the glorification of believers as they are called into a special relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 66, 5, 8, 14, 'I am glorified in them', 'Glory and Worship of the Lamb', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of Jesus and the worship he receives. In John 17:10, Jesus speaks of being glorified in his followers, while Revelation 5:8-14 depicts the worship of the Lamb, highlighting his worthiness and glory.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 46, 3, 21, 23, 'all mine are thine, and thine are mine', 'Ownership and Glory in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ownership, stating that all things belong to believers through their connection to Christ. The phrase ''all mine are thine, and thine are mine'' in John parallels the declaration ''all things are yours'' in 1 Corinthians, highlighting the shared glory and possession between Christ, God, and believers.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 53, 1, 10, 10, 'I am glorified in them', 'Glorification in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification, with John 17:10 stating, ''I am glorified in them,'' and 2 Thessalonians 1:10 referring to being ''glorified in his saints.'' This connection highlights the shared focus on the relationship between Christ and believers in the context of glory.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 43, 16, 14, 15, 'I am glorified in them', 'Glorification and Ownership Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that all things belonging to the Father are also Jesus''s. The theme of glorification is central, as Jesus is glorified in those who belong to Him, and the Spirit will glorify Jesus by revealing what is His.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 10, 51, 1, 15, 19, 'I am glorified in them', 'Divine Ownership and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine ownership and glory. In John 17:10, Jesus speaks of glorification in relation to the Father and believers, while Colossians 1:19 emphasizes that all fullness dwells in Christ, indicating His preeminence and divine nature.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 40, 6, 9, 9, NULL, 'Unity in Prayer and Purpose', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine protection and unity among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s name and the relationship between the Father and those who follow Him.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 20, 18, 10, 10, 'thine own name', 'Safety in God''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the protective power of God''s name. In John 17:11, Jesus asks for the disciples to be kept through God''s name, while Proverbs 18:10 describes the name of the Lord as a strong tower for safety.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 43, 17, 12, 18, 'that they may be one, as we are', 'Unity and Protection in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of unity among believers and the need for divine protection. The request for believers to be kept ''one'' connects with the prayer for their protection from evil while they are in the world.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 43, 17, 21, 22, 'that they may be one, as we are', 'Unity in Christ''s Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of unity among believers. The call for them to be ''one'' reflects the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting the importance of this unity for the world''s belief.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 58, 9, 24, 24, 'that they may be one', 'Unity and Divine Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ''s relationship with God and His followers. Both passages emphasize the idea of being in the presence of God, with John focusing on unity among believers and Hebrews on Christ appearing before God for them.', 'theme', 0.384, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 49, 4, 4, 4, 'that they may be one', 'Unity in the Body of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of being one, as seen in ''that they may be one'' and ''one body.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 11, 50, 2, 9, 9, 'that they may be one, as we are', 'Unity and Exaltation of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity and the significance of the name of Jesus. In John 17:11, the call for oneness among believers reflects the divine relationship, while Philippians 2:9 emphasizes the exaltation of Jesus'' name, which is above every name.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 12, 19, 109, 6, 19, 'son of perdition', 'Judgment and Betrayal Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment against the wicked. John 17:12 references the ''son of perdition,'' paralleling the condemnation and curses laid out in Psalms 109:6-19.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
